# ShepitNote participant roster — known people for the meeting summarizer.
#
# Copy this file to roster.txt (same directory, git-ignored because it matches
# *.txt) and edit it. The summarizer folds these names + roles into the notes as
# GROUND TRUTH, so it stops inventing roles, splitting one person across two
# names, or listing people who were only mentioned but never actually spoke.
#
# One person per line:
#     Name | role | alias1, alias2, ...
# The role and aliases columns are optional:
#     Roman | scrum master
#     Alik
# A leading '*' marks YOU — the local recorder (the microphone / "You" track).
# You can instead set MEETING_SELF_NAME / MEETING_SELF_ROLE in .shepitnoterc.
# Lines starting with '#' and blank lines are ignored.
#
# Aliases capture diminutives and other-script spellings, so the model treats
# "Витя", "Vitya" and "Viktor" as the SAME person and normalizes to "Viktor".

* Your Name | your role |
# Viktor | frontend developer | Витя, Виктор, Vitya
# Eduard | dev lead | Эдуард
# Roman  | scrum master / facilitator | Роман
# Alik   | engineer | Алик
